Instead of using inheritance for code reuse, it'd be cleaner to model this as a method that takes a callback to abstract newSetOperationNode. Then, you can pass an inline lambda which does the appropriate new XXXNode as the callback. Something like:
public static SetOperationNode flatten(SetOperationNode node, Context context, NodeInstantiator instantiator)
{
    if (flattening not necessary) {
        return null;
    }   
    ...
    return instantiator.create(....);
}
(NodeInstantiator would be a single-method interface that takes the arguments needed to instantiate an IntersectNode, UnionNode, etc)
and in the rule:
SetOperationNode result = flatten(node, IntersectNode::new);
if (result != null) {
    return Optional.ofPlanNode(result);
}

